{"id":"4989","name":"Siri Homebridge Manager","tagline":"Manage your Homebridge server using natural language commands!","icon":"ios14 c-1448498689 g61483","latest":"22167","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<h1>Siri Homebridge Manager</h1>\n<h3>Manage Homebridge with Siri</h3>\n<p><img alt=\"Homebridge\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3979615/78016493-9b89a800-7396-11ea-9442-414ad9ffcdf2.png\" title=\"HB\"></p>\n<p>What does this do? Well the answer is simple. This is a shortcut that allows you to manage your Homebridge instance using Siri and Natural Language. Here are the full feature sets!</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Restart Homebridge service</li>\n<li>Reboot your server </li>\n<li>Check the online status of your instance (is Homebridge running?)</li>\n<li>Check your Server's Internet connection</li>\n<li>Perform an ISP Speed Test (macOS and Pi Users only. this uses a brew tool called \"speedtest-cli\")</li>\n<li>Check the CPU temperature on your server (macOS, Linux and Pi users only. macOS users need to use a brew tool called \"osx-cpu-temp\")</li>\n<li>You can delete your configuration by telling it to \"restore the shortcut\" this deletes your configuration.</li>\n<li>run a diagnostic</li>\n<li>string up to 2 commands at a time</li>\n<li>you can feed commands with other shortcuts to “shortcut” to actions within it</li>\n<li>Get RAM usage</li>\n<li>Get CPU load</li>\n<li>Force Restart Homebridge (restart UI and Service)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you ever need a little help on what you can do, you can say \"Help Me\" and Siri will tell you all the available actions :)</p>\n<h3>Coming Soon...</h3>\n<p>The roadmap for this shortcut is rather clear. As this is the initial release, there is a bit of room to grow. Here is what we have planned!</p>\n<ul>\n<li>A repair instance tool</li>\n<li>Backup feature</li>\n</ul>\n<p>this shortcut uses LightningEmbed for updating! no need to install an alternate updater.</p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>4.1 - Oct. 23, 2020, 3:37 p.m.</strong></p><p>Version 4.1 Release Notes<br><br>- Docker support BayBee! Finally Docker users can restart their container and manage their instance just say “reboot my server” as it’s in the same command chain.<br>- ISP Speed testing now includes Upload<br>- users can now Force Restart Home-bridge (this restarts the service and UI) after executing, the shortcut will exit.<br>- after rebooting the server, the shortcut will exit.<br><br>- Total Actions: #547<br>- Created on iOS 14.2<br>- Released at Oct 23, 2020</p>"}